Valley Heights will be allowed 150 tickets for the HS FB game in Marysville this week. Once the players families have purchased theirs, the remaining tickets will be available starting Wednesday morning on a first come first serve basis. $5.00 for adults and $3.00 for students. You can purchase your tickets in the HS office.
ALL TICKETS WILL BE PRE-SOLD. NO WALK UP TICKETS.
ALL FANS WILL ENTER ON THE EAST SIDE OF THE STADIUM (OFF 12 TH STREET-DUE TO CONSTRUCTION).
FANS ARE EXPECTED TO FOLLOW ALL OF THE USD 364 COVID GUIDELINES AND PROTOCOLS.
-Masks must be worn at the gate to gain entry into the stadium.
-Spectators are required to follow social distancing guidelines.
-Spectators can remove mask if social distancing can be followed.
-Masks will be required if needed to enter the school for restrooms or concession stand.
- Spectators will not be allowed on the field/track or near teams before, after and during play.
- Concessions will be limited to drinks and pre-packaged items.

post_text:
We are so excited to get students back into the building to kick off our 2020-2021 school year! Many of you are familiar with our after school program known as Colt's Round-Up (CRU). We are getting a little later start this year than normal but we are happy to release our first semester online registration. Students will attend CRU in Blue Rapids or Waterville Elementary based upon their home address. They must be onsite learners and students will ride their normal bus at the end of the school day. There will be no transportation at 5:30 when CRU dismisses.
Please fill out a form for each student who will be attending. Registration will close after August 26th.
https://forms.gle/hxfu1egcQx6Yf3So9

post_text:
The day is FINALLY here, Graduation Day 2020!
Below are a few of the details for attending the graduation ceremony:
Ceremony will be on the VH football field beginning at 11:00 a.m., Saturday, July 25.
Attendees are highly encouraged to wear masks and/or keep social distancing between families.
Please remain in your seat for the duration of the ceremony. The VH journalism staff will provide two photographers to take pictures during the ceremony. All pictures will be shared through the VH Facebook page. You are more than welcome to save any pictures that are taken.
There will not be a congratulatory processional line following the graduation ceremony.
Finally, we will be using Facebook Live to stream the ceremony. We recognize that not all family members and guests feel comfortable traveling or attending larger groups. It will be available through Facebook Live.

Summer learning opportunity for 3rd - 8th grade girls!

FREE GIRLS ROCK STEAM CAMP!

WSU Tech is hosting our 5th annual Girls Rock STEAM Camp on July 21st ‚Äì 22nd for 3rd-8th graders.

This year the camp is FREE, thanks to the generosity of our sponsors, and will be brought to your HOME, courtesy of COVID-19!

Using new technology brought to us by WSU Tech‚Äôs CareerCONNECT platform, powered by Nepris, girls will be able to view and interact live with professionals in STEAM fields on any computer, tablet or mobile device during an interesting and engaging camp specifically geared to 3rd ‚Äì 8th graders.

post_text: As the Valley Heights KAY sponsor I get the opportunity to work with a great bunch of students. We organize a lot of activities in the community and school. I am looking forward to continuing these activities for the next school year. Having said that, I am happy to announce the 2020-21 KAY officers are: Emma Toerber, President, Emma Yungeberg, Vice-President, Maecyn Gunn, Secretary, and Abigail Steinfort, Stuco Rep. Also, as most of you know, Mrs. Oatney will be retiring at the end of the year, and we will miss her as a co-sponsor!

post_text:
Following Governor Kelly's recent release, when Phase 3 begins, June 15, this will allow summer camps to be held starting on that day. This change is based upon the current guidelines and is subject to change.
Right now this change only affects June Camp. Families with students attending summer school sessions will be contacted by staff to inform you of times for face to face sessions in Blue Rapids or Waterville beginning June 8th.
We will still be serving lunches and breakfast at our normal pickup times in each location Monday - Thursday at both elementary schools.
We understand this is a very tough situation and we will continue to keep you informed as we work to serve the families of our district.
The link to the registration form for June and July is below. You only need to fill it out if you have not already registered your student.

https://forms.gle/pbcYA2CgfmdMxHir9

post_text:
The 2020 Valley Heights Graduation Ceremony has been rescheduled.
Given the restrictions we are currently operating under, there is no possible way to hold graduation ceremonies in May unless it was done virtually. We are cautiously optimistic that by moving graduation for the class of 2020 to Saturday, July 25th, beginning at 11:00 a.m., it will increase the likelihood that some of the social gathering restrictions will be released and we will be able to hold graduation ceremonies. While we hope that those ceremonies are more traditional in nature, we must be prepared to adjust the ceremonies to meet any social distancing requirements and crowd size limitations that we are operating under at the time. Hopefully, with some flexibility, we are able to offer the Class of 2020 a traditional graduation ceremony!

post_text: Forensic Science students are studying insects of death, the insects that are attracted to decaying flesh. Below is Gates Carder‚Äôs experiment. She put raw chicken into a vented container and has it hanging outside in her yard. She takes daily pictures to determine which insects arrive and in what sequence. The project is due May 1st. It will be interesting to see her results.

post_text: The Valley Heights National Honor Society is proud to announce that Sam Hardin has been selected as a NHS Scholarship recipient. text: Mr. Bergkamp‚Äôs statement about school 3/18/2020.

post_text:
Hello Valley Heights:
Today the Governor suspended school as we currently know it until the end of May. We are receiving guidance from the Kansas Department of Education on how we are to proceed with delivering instruction to our students. The Legislature has also approved for districts to apply for waivers that will mandate two things. 1) Continuous Learning Plans are to be developed and delivered to students. 2) All hourly employees will be paid.
The following schedule will apply to Valley Heights schools:
March 23 - 27 - Staff will develop instructional delivery methods. NO instruction will be provided this week.
March 30th. Instructional delivery methods will be implemented.
Please stay tuned for more specific instructions on how we will deliver our Continuous Learning Plans.
text:

Today the Governor suspended school as we currently know it until the end of May. We are receiving guidance from the Kansas Department of Education on how we are to proceed with delivering instruction to our students. The Legislature has also approved for districts to apply for waivers that will mandate two things. 1) Continuous Learning Plans are to be developed and delivered to students. 2) All hourly employees will be paid.
The following schedule will apply to Valley Heights schools:
March 23 - 27 - Staff will develop instructional delivery methods. NO instruction will be provided this week.
March 30th. Instructional delivery methods will be implemented.
Please stay tuned for more specific instructions on how we will deliver our Continuous Learning Plans.
